observations.recommendation:
1. The Municipal Accountant to:
a. effect the following suggested adjusting entries to correct the BGCM Fund balance as of December 31, 2020: Dr. Prior Year’s Adjustments- ₱1,694,958.19 Cr. Trust Liability – BGCM - ₱1,694,958.19 Trust Fund Books: Dr. Cash in Bank – ₱1,218,629.65 Cr. Trust Liability – DRRM – ₱ 1,218,629.65 #To transfer the unexpended DRRM-MOOE to STF General Fund Books: Dr. Cash in Bank – ₱19,729.10 Cr. Trust Liability – DRRM – ₱ 19,729.10 Trust Fund Books: Dr. Government Equity – ₱19,729.10 Cr. Cash in Bank –P 19,729.10 #To revert the CY 2013 DRRM-STF to General Fund
b. henceforth, ensure that BGCM FS are based only on duly booked transactions concerning the fund, and make certain monitoring and complete recording of transactions until the fund is fully utilized or reverted, whichever comes first;
c. cause the prompt liquidation of the unliquidated cash advance of Mr. Robert M. Baggong at year end amounting to noted cash amounting to P1,493,268.50, and intensify efforts to liquidate all cash advances at year end to ensure the correct reporting of financial performance during the year;
d. henceforth, comply with the required certification imposed by Paragraph 1.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 on all cash advances, attesting that previous cash advances have been liquidated and accounted for in the books, and refrain from further granting of cash advances to officials/employees with outstanding previous cash advances prior to liquidation thereof in line with Section 89 of P.D. 1445;
e. intensify internal control over the review and approval procedures applied in the granting and liquidation of cash advances including its supporting documents; f. intensify the pre-audit procedures and enforce prevailing guidelines on documentary requirements for procurement of goods prior to disbursement of funds to ensure the complete submission of supporting documents;
g. ensure that all claims against government funds shall be supported with appropriate and complete documentation.
2. The Local Development Council (LDC) to prepare the Supplemental Investment Program for COVID-19 related PPAs undertaken in CY 2020, to be approved by the local sanggunian, in compliance to DILG-DBM JMC No. 02 dtd Mar 30, 2020.
3. The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) and the end-user units to take appropriate action on the deficient Omnibus Sworn Statement for the procurement of medicines and comply all of the lacking supporting documents noted in Annex E of the CY 2020 AAR, otherwise shall be disallowed in audit.
4. The Municipal Mayor to: a. Enforce strict compliance of the required supporting documents in availing of cash advances its liquidation thereof, and procurement of goods by all officers and employees of the LGU, particularly those whose functions allows them to, in the exigency of service; and b. ensure that all applicable laws, rules and regulations pertaining to financial reporting, operation and compliance are steadfastly observed by the LGU to foster fairness in the financial statements and to safeguard the funds of the LGU.

The Municipal Accountant to:
1. Intensify liquidation of cash advances by consistently and regularly issuing demand letters to the concerned officers and employees, both active and inactive, through the responsible Accounting Staff in-charge of the cash advances;
2. Require immediate refund of cash advances through salary deductions, if necessary.
3. Refrain from further granting cash advances to officials/employees with outstanding advances prior to liquidation thereof in line with Section 89 of PD 1445, among others;
4. Expedite evaluation of complied liquidation reports with respect to the long outstanding cash advances for Confidential Fund and thereafter effect the liquidation thereof by derecognizing in the books the corresponding amount in accordance with COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-001 dated January 8, 2015; and
5. Henceforth, adhere strictly with the prescribed laws, rules and regulations in the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances in order to safeguard the funds of the local government, recognize all expenses within the applicable fiscal year and thus present fairly the financial statements.

